The Russian army dropped bombs on a residential area of Mariupol, Donetsk region. Russian tanks are also advancing along the line of contact. "Today at around 12:00 the Russian army fired again at civilians in the Left Bank district of Mariupol. Several bombs were dropped on apartment buildings, "the city hall said. The city is developing a plan to evacuate people from the Left Bank district. living in the perimeter of the shelling.    From the airport in Sumy, the Russian military fired on a civilian car. In the car two adults and three young children, including an infant. The woman who was wounded in the head died. There is also another woman who died near the airport. Fighting is taking place in the city itself and in the villages of Nizy, Bezdryk and Konotop in the Sumy region.    In Nikolaev, the south of the country, bridges are built after the message that from the Crimea from the direction of Nikolaev the column of the Russian equipment moves. "We are building bridges, dismantling e-government systems in them. Also, just in case, they are mined and, in case of a breakthrough by Russian forces, will be blown up, "said Mayor Oleksandr Senkevych.    As of 1 p.m. on February 27, Russian troops had launched five air and 16 missile strikes on Ukrainian territory. Currently, the shelling of Kharkiv and Balakliia continues, the defence of Kherson continues, according to the General Staff of the Armed Forces of Ukraine. According to the agency, the Russian army is currently continuing an air offensive, during which it is shelling military and civilian infrastructure.
